1
00:00:55,132 --> 00:00:57,592
Hurry! She collapsed ten minutes ago.

2
00:01:32,711 --> 00:01:34,253
The ambulance is here.

3
00:02:02,574 --> 00:02:05,743
<i>Saint Theresa, my sweet Jesus,
don't abandon me,</i>

4
00:02:05,994 --> 00:02:09,121
<i>give me strength, I want to go on living.</i>

5
00:02:09,456 --> 00:02:11,707
<i>Bring me back to life.</i>

6
00:02:35,148 --> 00:02:36,023
Why are you crying?

7
00:02:36,233 --> 00:02:37,817
Scram you brats!

8
00:02:42,322 --> 00:02:45,199
<i>♪  I feel gloomy</i>

9
00:02:45,409 --> 00:02:48,327
<i>♪  It's not new to me</i>

10
00:02:48,537 --> 00:02:51,208
<i>♪  So melancholy</i>

11
00:02:51,284 --> 00:02:53,075
<i>♪  There's nothing I can do</i>

12
00:02:55,085 --> 00:02:57,586
What are you doing here?

13
00:02:57,796 --> 00:02:59,005
Why are you crying?

14
00:02:59,881 --> 00:03:01,215
Are you all alone?

15
00:03:02,301 --> 00:03:04,427
Where's your mommy?

16
00:03:05,971 --> 00:03:09,140
<i>♪  Again and again</i>

17
00:03:09,391 --> 00:03:12,476
<i>♪  I drag this chain</i>

18
00:03:12,769 --> 00:03:15,438
<i>♪  of sorrow and pain</i>

19
00:03:15,647 --> 00:03:18,232
<i>♪  and nothing more</i>

20
00:03:18,817 --> 00:03:21,902
<i>♪  It's not new to me</i>

21
00:03:22,154 --> 00:03:25,072
<i>♪  So melancholy</i>

22
00:03:25,282 --> 00:03:28,826
<i>♪  I feel gloomy</i>

23
00:03:29,036 --> 00:03:31,912
Some mother. You deserve to be strung up!

24
00:03:32,164 --> 00:03:34,457
I have to live. I'm a singer!

25
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:35,791
Look at your daughter!

26
00:03:36,084 --> 00:03:38,044
I take very good care of her!

27
00:03:48,096 --> 00:03:50,931
<i>Louis, I can't go on waiting for you like this.</i>

28
00:03:51,350 --> 00:03:53,142
<i>Belleville's unbearable.</i>

29
00:03:54,186 --> 00:03:56,187
<i>An impresario said with my talent</i>

30
00:03:56,396 --> 00:04:00,316
<i>I should try Constantinople
like the singer Frehel...</i>

31
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,902
Good news for our acrobat?

32
00:04:03,945 --> 00:04:07,281
Sure... Commendations from Clemenceau.

33
00:04:14,456 --> 00:04:16,415
<i>I left Edith with my mother.</i>

34
00:04:16,792 --> 00:04:20,252
<i>Mamma Aicha will keep her
until my career takes off.</i>

35
00:04:21,088 --> 00:04:24,382
<i>Louis, I've stopped waiting for you.</i>

36
00:04:25,717 --> 00:04:27,051
<i>Anetta.</i>

37
00:04:50,992 --> 00:04:52,159
Anybody home?

38
00:05:26,778 --> 00:05:31,073
Edith?

39
00:05:37,038 --> 00:05:38,164
Louis?

40
00:05:43,044 --> 00:05:44,003
Enough's enough.

41
00:06:46,149 --> 00:06:47,149
What's this?

42
00:06:49,611 --> 00:06:50,694
Your grandchild...

43
00:06:51,863 --> 00:06:52,821
Edith.

44
00:06:56,451 --> 00:06:57,576
What a strange name.

45
00:07:06,127 --> 00:07:07,545
She's a sickly child.

46
00:07:11,132 --> 00:07:12,383
Follow me.

47
00:07:23,144 --> 00:07:24,436
What are you doing here?

48
00:07:25,939 --> 00:07:28,148
You're so cute. What's your name?

49
00:07:28,608 --> 00:07:29,900
Back to work, Titine!

50
00:07:30,402 --> 00:07:32,653
Someone's in the upstairs toilet.

51
00:07:33,780 --> 00:07:35,197
You've beautiful blue eyes.

52
00:07:50,797 --> 00:07:51,880
I'm listening...

53
00:07:54,551 --> 00:07:55,676
I have to go back.

54
00:07:57,804 --> 00:08:01,682
I'll be demobilized soon.
Then I'll go back to the circus.

55
00:08:03,685 --> 00:08:05,019
I came to see my cherub.

56
00:08:05,478 --> 00:08:06,312
Get out.

57
00:08:06,521 --> 00:08:08,063
I'm all done, Mamma Louise.

58
00:08:08,273 --> 00:08:09,607
Tend the door.

59
00:08:16,281 --> 00:08:17,323
Where's her mother?

60
00:08:19,034 --> 00:08:19,867
I don't know.

61
00:08:24,956 --> 00:08:26,081
Want to leave her here?

62
00:08:29,210 --> 00:08:30,336
People will gossip.

63
00:08:31,046 --> 00:08:32,504
People always gossip.

64
00:09:10,835 --> 00:09:12,127
Aren't we taking her to church?

65
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:17,174
We'll miss mass.

66
00:09:17,467 --> 00:09:20,302
The earth doesn't revolve around her.

67
00:09:27,936 --> 00:09:29,687
Heard we're keeping a baby.

68
00:09:29,896 --> 00:09:31,105
Can we see her?

69
00:09:31,564 --> 00:09:33,607
She's a little girl. Want bread?

70
00:09:33,817 --> 00:09:35,192
Everyone out of here.

71
00:09:38,363 --> 00:09:40,114
Go on, ask her to sing.

72
00:09:42,534 --> 00:09:46,161
You'd be on stage, but your hair's too red.

73
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:52,543
<i>♪  One night I went for a swim</i>

74
00:09:52,752 --> 00:09:54,670
<i>♪  Wearing only my bare skin</i>

75
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:58,549
<i>♪  No one was there to see</i>

76
00:09:58,758 --> 00:10:00,843
<i>♪  Except the dark night sky</i>

77
00:10:01,052 --> 00:10:03,345
<i>♪  Then the moon came out to shine</i>

78
00:10:03,555 --> 00:10:06,640
<i>♪  I asked it to caress me, baby</i>

79
00:10:06,850 --> 00:10:09,476
<i>♪  When I heard nearby</i>

80
00:10:09,686 --> 00:10:11,770
<i>♪  A breathless cry</i>

81
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:15,482
<i>♪  There was a man upon a rock</i>

82
00:10:15,692 --> 00:10:17,151
<i>♪  Looking down at me</i>

83
00:10:17,527 --> 00:10:19,361
<i>♪  The man went 'oh!'</i>

84
00:10:19,946 --> 00:10:22,156
<i>♪  And me in the water</i>

85
00:10:22,490 --> 00:10:25,242
<i>♪  I said 'oh...'</i>

86
00:10:25,452 --> 00:10:28,746
<i>♪  He saw me nude...</i>

87
00:10:28,955 --> 00:10:33,375
<i>♪  With nothing to hold up or hide behind</i>

88
00:10:33,585 --> 00:10:36,795
<i>♪  I blushed all night long</i>

89
00:10:37,005 --> 00:10:41,258
<i>♪  He saw me nude</i>

90
00:10:41,509 --> 00:10:43,802
<i>♪  Quite nude</i>

91
00:10:44,012 --> 00:10:47,473
<i>♪  Out of human decency</i>

92
00:10:47,682 --> 00:10:50,517
<i>♪  I covered my face with my two hands</i>

93
00:10:50,727 --> 00:10:53,729
<i>♪  But now it's clear</i>

94
00:10:53,938 --> 00:10:56,523
<i>♪  With my careless gesture of fear</i>

95
00:10:56,775 --> 00:10:59,943
<i>♪  I forgot to hide</i>

96
00:11:00,153 --> 00:11:03,989
<i>♪  My sweet little backside</i>

97
00:11:04,282 --> 00:11:11,663
<i>♪  He saw me nude... totally nude...</i>

98
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:29,389
Titine!

99
00:11:29,808 --> 00:11:32,142
Titine, open up. Enough of this!

100
00:11:32,435 --> 00:11:34,728
- Now what?
- She's with Edith.

101
00:11:35,396 --> 00:11:36,814
Open this door, now!

102
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:38,273
What's going on?

103
00:11:38,483 --> 00:11:42,194
Nothing! Get ready,
the gentlemen will be here soon.

104
00:11:43,655 --> 00:11:46,782
- Open up or else!
- I can't work.

105
00:11:48,201 --> 00:11:50,577
- I can't work!
- Really!

106
00:11:50,787 --> 00:11:53,163
You think this is a hotel?

107
00:11:53,873 --> 00:11:56,625
I'm keeping Edith. I'm keeping her.

108
00:11:57,126 --> 00:11:58,502
That's what you think!

109
00:11:59,462 --> 00:12:01,922
It's me, open up.

110
00:12:02,423 --> 00:12:04,049
Your Legionnaire's here.

111
00:12:04,259 --> 00:12:05,384
I don't care.

112
00:12:05,885 --> 00:12:08,929
He's a liar. He tells me nothing but lies.

113
00:12:09,347 --> 00:12:11,390
Titine, stop this right now.

114
00:12:11,599 --> 00:12:15,018
Come out or you'll be on the street so fast!

115
00:12:15,228 --> 00:12:17,145
Enough of your antics!

116
00:12:29,284 --> 00:12:30,868
I don't want trouble.

117
00:12:53,683 --> 00:12:54,766
Doug!

118
00:13:00,189 --> 00:13:02,065
What? Are you jealous?

119
00:13:03,651 --> 00:13:06,445
I sent your Billie Holiday records to the hotel.

120
00:13:06,654 --> 00:13:07,529
Thank you, Loulou.

121
00:13:07,947 --> 00:13:11,033
Billie and I were born the same year. Funny!

122
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:16,038
I brought my sketches.

123
00:13:17,415 --> 00:13:19,791
Do you want to see them now or later?

124
00:13:20,460 --> 00:13:23,837
Later. I've got to sing that fool's song.

125
00:13:26,049 --> 00:13:26,882
Before your time...

126
00:13:27,383 --> 00:13:28,133
What?

127
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:29,885
Forget it.

128
00:13:32,263 --> 00:13:33,263
Let's go.

129
00:13:58,414 --> 00:13:59,289
I'm ready.

130
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:01,458
Let's go.

131
00:14:17,225 --> 00:14:19,393
<i>♪  Come right in, Milord</i>

132
00:14:19,602 --> 00:14:21,770
<i>♪  Sit down at my table</i>

133
00:14:21,980 --> 00:14:24,398
<i>♪  It's freezing cold outside</i>

134
00:14:24,607 --> 00:14:26,274
<i>♪  Here it's more comfortable</i>

135
00:14:26,484 --> 00:14:28,610
<i>♪  Make yourself at home, Milord</i>

136
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:30,946
<i>♪  Leave your cares with me</i>

137
00:14:31,155 --> 00:14:33,323
<i>♪  Relax, you'll be at ease</i>

138
00:14:33,616 --> 00:14:35,450
<i>♪  Put your feet up, feel free</i>

139
00:14:35,660 --> 00:14:37,744
<i>♪  I know you well, Milord</i>

140
00:14:37,954 --> 00:14:40,038
<i>♪  Although you don't know me</i>

141
00:14:40,248 --> 00:14:42,833
<i>♪  A mere girl of the port</i>

142
00:14:43,042 --> 00:14:47,212
<i>♪  A shadow of the street...</i>

143
00:14:48,548 --> 00:14:51,049
<i>♪  I passed quite close to you</i>

144
00:14:51,342 --> 00:14:53,844
<i>♪  In the street yesterday</i>

145
00:14:54,137 --> 00:14:56,972
<i>♪  You looked so full of pride</i>

146
00:14:57,181 --> 00:14:59,307
<i>♪  The man with everything</i>

147
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,893
<i>♪  Your lovely silken scarf</i>

148
00:15:02,145 --> 00:15:04,813
<i>♪  Floating all around your shoulders</i>

149
00:15:05,023 --> 00:15:07,774
<i>♪  You seemed on top of the world</i>

150
00:15:07,984 --> 00:15:11,111
<i>♪  One might say a king</i>

151
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:13,822
<i>♪  Marching like a victor</i>

152
00:15:14,032 --> 00:15:16,950
<i>♪  A lady on your arm</i>

153
00:15:17,452 --> 00:15:20,704
<i>♪  My God, she was so beautiful</i>

154
00:15:23,082 --> 00:15:24,041
It's Jeanne!

155
00:15:28,212 --> 00:15:29,671
Jeanne, what's wrong?

156
00:15:30,631 --> 00:15:31,381
There's blood...

157
00:15:31,591 --> 00:15:32,507
Talk to us!

158
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:36,511
He wanted to play doctor, with his instruments.

159
00:15:36,721 --> 00:15:37,929
The bastard!

160
00:15:40,808 --> 00:15:41,767
Titine!

161
00:15:42,393 --> 00:15:43,727
We must tell Madam.

162
00:15:43,936 --> 00:15:46,521
She'll kill me. It hurts.

163
00:15:49,317 --> 00:15:50,901
I can't see!

164
00:16:10,588 --> 00:16:13,590
- Well, Doctor?
- Her health's fragile.

165
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:16,384
It's her cornea. She has keratitis.

166
00:16:18,012 --> 00:16:18,887
Is she blind?

167
00:16:20,223 --> 00:16:21,431
It's an inflammation.

168
00:16:22,892 --> 00:16:25,143
Be patient. It takes months.

169
00:16:26,187 --> 00:16:28,772
Take this to the pharmacy.

170
00:16:30,525 --> 00:16:31,399
Thank you.

171
00:16:32,235 --> 00:16:33,401
Whose child is she?

172
00:16:35,863 --> 00:16:36,947
Nobody's.

173
00:17:23,286 --> 00:17:26,163
Theresa, I rarely ask anything of you,

174
00:17:26,664 --> 00:17:28,582
I only ask that you hear little Edith.

175
00:17:29,876 --> 00:17:32,919
Go on, Edith. Speak to her. She'll listen.

176
00:17:33,379 --> 00:17:34,421
Go ahead.

177
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:36,464
Theresa,

178
00:17:37,133 --> 00:17:40,010
I don't want to be blind. I want to see.

179
00:17:40,219 --> 00:17:41,303
She's all bruised.

180
00:17:41,762 --> 00:17:42,596
Go on.

181
00:17:43,139 --> 00:17:46,516
I want to learn to read, and run like before.

182
00:17:46,809 --> 00:17:48,101
I don't want to be blind.

183
00:17:48,311 --> 00:17:52,314
Saint Theresa,
tell baby Jesus to look after Edith.

184
00:17:53,274 --> 00:17:54,107
Go ahead.

185
00:17:55,067 --> 00:17:57,736
Thank you Saint Theresa and Jesus.

186
00:17:58,196 --> 00:18:00,071
Thank you.

187
00:18:37,193 --> 00:18:38,777
This is it. You're here, Edith.

188
00:20:05,823 --> 00:20:06,990
She can see...

189
00:20:08,868 --> 00:20:10,076
She can see!

190
00:20:19,503 --> 00:20:20,587
Titine, get up!

191
00:20:21,589 --> 00:20:22,422
What is it?

192
00:20:22,631 --> 00:20:24,466
He's back. He's taking Edith.

193
00:20:25,217 --> 00:20:26,051
Get dressed.

194
00:20:26,844 --> 00:20:29,137
They can't do that to me!

195
00:20:29,472 --> 00:20:31,556
How can you go back to that job?

196
00:20:32,558 --> 00:20:33,683
She'll see the country.

197
00:20:34,435 --> 00:20:35,435
Go then.

198
00:20:37,271 --> 00:20:38,646
Edith!

199
00:20:38,856 --> 00:20:41,566
Titine!

200
00:20:42,318 --> 00:20:44,027
Don't take my little girl!

201
00:20:44,236 --> 00:20:46,321
Let her go!

202
00:20:46,530 --> 00:20:48,156
Enough!

203
00:20:48,366 --> 00:20:49,783
She's mad!

204
00:20:50,201 --> 00:20:51,743
Stop it or you're out!

205
00:20:51,952 --> 00:20:53,953
You have no right!

206
00:21:00,378 --> 00:21:01,669
Don't do this to me!

207
00:21:01,879 --> 00:21:03,671
Go!

208
00:21:12,807 --> 00:21:14,224
I'll kill myself.

209
00:21:20,773 --> 00:21:21,689
We're at Orly airport.

210
00:21:23,943 --> 00:21:26,111
Passengers are disembarking.
I see her. It's Edith Piaf!

211
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:28,071
A young man's on her arm.

212
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:30,323
What did you bring from America?

213
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:31,574
An American.

214
00:21:31,909 --> 00:21:32,909
What's his name?

215
00:21:33,828 --> 00:21:36,496
Edith, please!

216
00:21:37,248 --> 00:21:40,750
Like her song,
she's "carried away by the crowd"...

217
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:43,795
She steps into her elegant black and white car.

218
00:21:45,339 --> 00:21:47,924
She looks tired, but is all smiles.

219
00:21:55,015 --> 00:21:57,350
Silence! I propose a toast...

220
00:21:57,726 --> 00:21:59,519
What a slob!

221
00:21:59,979 --> 00:22:01,229
Slob yourself.

222
00:22:02,857 --> 00:22:04,732
Indulge the invalid.

223
00:22:06,444 --> 00:22:10,613
Watch out accordion man or you'll get a shiner!

224
00:22:12,241 --> 00:22:13,575
Perfect timing!

225
00:22:13,784 --> 00:22:16,995
Call the boss. I want free champagne!

226
00:22:17,455 --> 00:22:20,290
I'm Edith Piaf, and I made a mess.

227
00:22:21,417 --> 00:22:24,836
Everyone kiss. Even enemies!

228
00:22:25,254 --> 00:22:26,337
Kiss me, Claude.

229
00:22:35,764 --> 00:22:38,016
- Who's that broad?
- No idea.

230
00:22:38,225 --> 00:22:39,934
Who gets the steak tartare?

231
00:22:40,144 --> 00:22:42,604
Where did your handsome friend go?

232
00:22:42,813 --> 00:22:44,355
Don't embarrass her...

233
00:22:44,565 --> 00:22:46,983
Butt out Coquatrix, who rang your bell?

234
00:22:47,485 --> 00:22:49,694
Well... Mademoiselle!

235
00:22:49,904 --> 00:22:54,032
Miss Piaf, a pleasure! What can I do for you?

236
00:22:54,617 --> 00:22:56,951
A lot. I want a present.

237
00:22:57,453 --> 00:22:58,244
Naturally.

238
00:22:58,704 --> 00:22:59,704
Well...

239
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:03,374
I wanted champagne, but I'll take a ring,

240
00:23:03,626 --> 00:23:06,961
a big ring with diamonds studded everywhere.

241
00:23:07,171 --> 00:23:09,172
Don't trouble yourself, we'll have champagne.

242
00:23:11,383 --> 00:23:14,427
Here's a toast to the love I have for you all.

243
00:23:14,803 --> 00:23:16,846
And I'll stand up for that.

244
00:23:17,056 --> 00:23:18,348
Give me a hand.

245
00:23:22,603 --> 00:23:26,272
I'd like to make a toast to Marguerite.

246
00:23:27,775 --> 00:23:32,362
My composer, and my most loyal friend
in the business.

247
00:23:33,364 --> 00:23:37,116
Don't blush like that, you'll make us cry.

248
00:23:53,717 --> 00:23:54,842
You want an autograph?

249
00:23:55,386 --> 00:23:56,719
I don't think so.

250
00:23:59,348 --> 00:24:03,059
Bubbles and booze, perfect.
This is Claude's influence.

251
00:24:03,269 --> 00:24:04,852
You're irritating, Loulou.

252
00:24:05,396 --> 00:24:08,731
We're just back to Paris, we had some fun.

253
00:24:12,027 --> 00:24:14,195
Don't play the broken hearted lover.

254
00:24:18,576 --> 00:24:20,702
I'm waiting for someone. Get lost.

255
00:24:21,620 --> 00:24:23,496
Let me remind you, you have commitments.

256
00:24:24,373 --> 00:24:25,540
You're not alone.

257
00:24:26,292 --> 00:24:29,127
Remember the first night at Gerny's?

258
00:24:30,546 --> 00:24:34,299
I was a bum. She looked at me like a princess.

259
00:24:34,508 --> 00:24:37,260
You were a princess. My princess!

260
00:24:37,886 --> 00:24:40,263
To Marguerite!

261
00:24:40,848 --> 00:24:43,433
To those who want to see me fall on my face.

262
00:24:43,934 --> 00:24:46,394
They think I don't notice! Cheers.

