1341
02:02:58,198 --> 02:03:00,407
I wanted to see his watch.

1342
02:03:19,844 --> 02:03:21,011
That's some face!

1343
02:03:23,431 --> 02:03:24,640
You've got wild eyes.

1344
02:03:28,728 --> 02:03:30,103
The kid's not so bad.

1345
02:04:05,223 --> 02:04:06,306
Simone.

1346
02:04:06,683 --> 02:04:07,849
Yes, Edith?

1347
02:04:10,770 --> 02:04:12,229
I didn't pray.

1348
02:04:16,150 --> 02:04:17,943
I want to pray on my knees.

1349
02:04:19,529 --> 02:04:22,948
No one will reproach you
if you're not on your knees.

1350
02:04:24,117 --> 02:04:26,535
I want to pray for my daddy.

1351
02:05:30,183 --> 02:05:34,144
Marcelle...

1352
02:05:35,438 --> 02:05:37,022
My little ghost.

1353
02:05:39,525 --> 02:05:42,110
Only Momone knows about it.

1354
02:05:42,320 --> 02:05:44,404
I need to tell you about my child.

1355
02:05:44,614 --> 02:05:45,656
Take it easy, Edith.

1356
02:05:45,865 --> 02:05:56,291
Marcelle!

1357
02:05:56,501 --> 02:05:59,920
Marcelle, go to bed. I've had enough today.

1358
02:06:00,129 --> 02:06:03,674
Think I can keep an eye out
for the cops and your kid?

1359
02:06:04,133 --> 02:06:05,926
What the hell's Louis doing?

1360
02:06:07,762 --> 02:06:09,262
It's him. Your father.

1361
02:06:14,102 --> 02:06:15,018
Did she eat?

1362
02:06:15,728 --> 02:06:18,313
<i>They said you were on the street with her!</i>

1363
02:06:18,731 --> 02:06:19,439
<i>Who said?</i>

1364
02:06:19,774 --> 02:06:22,776
<i>You get her twice a month and you screw up!</i>

1365
02:06:22,985 --> 02:06:25,028
I said not the streets!

1366
02:06:34,747 --> 02:06:35,747
Come quick!

1367
02:06:38,418 --> 02:06:40,168
It's Marcelle! Come on!

1368
02:06:44,006 --> 02:06:45,716
Marcelle's in the hospital!

1369
02:07:08,406 --> 02:07:09,531
Are you her mother?

1370
02:07:11,033 --> 02:07:13,618
Meningitis. Nothing could be done.

1371
02:07:14,120 --> 02:07:15,454
I'm sorry.

1372
02:07:50,531 --> 02:07:51,531
Edith,

1373
02:07:53,493 --> 02:07:54,785
I have the cross.

1374
02:08:12,220 --> 02:08:13,261
Hello.

1375
02:08:14,055 --> 02:08:15,931
They said you were on the beach.

1376
02:08:17,517 --> 02:08:19,518
Thank you for granting this interview.

1377
02:08:19,727 --> 02:08:21,061
My pleasure.

1378
02:08:22,814 --> 02:08:24,940
It's odd to see you so far from Paris.

1379
02:08:25,566 --> 02:08:27,275
I'm never far from Paris.

1380
02:08:28,861 --> 02:08:35,283
I've a list of questions. Just answer with
the first thing that comes to mind.

1381
02:08:38,579 --> 02:08:39,412
Well,

1382
02:08:40,540 --> 02:08:42,207
what is your favorite color?

1383
02:08:42,750 --> 02:08:43,625
Blue.

1384
02:08:44,418 --> 02:08:46,002
What's your favorite dish?

1385
02:08:46,504 --> 02:08:47,963
Pot roast.

1386
02:08:50,049 --> 02:08:52,717
Could you accept living a sensible life?

1387
02:08:53,261 --> 02:08:54,678
I already do.

1388
02:08:59,559 --> 02:09:01,518
<i>Who are your most faithful friends?</i>

1389
02:09:01,894 --> 02:09:04,145
<i>My true friends are faithful.</i>

1390
02:09:06,732 --> 02:09:08,775
<i>If you could no longer sing...</i>

1391
02:09:10,236 --> 02:09:13,071
<i>I could no longer live.</i>

1392
02:09:14,782 --> 02:09:16,157
<i>Are you afraid of death?</i>

1393
02:09:18,035 --> 02:09:19,786
<i>I fear loneliness more.</i>

1394
02:09:22,331 --> 02:09:23,248
<i>Do you pray?</i>

1395
02:09:23,583 --> 02:09:26,918
<i>Yes, because I believe in love.</i>

1396
02:09:28,296 --> 02:09:30,422
I don't want to go, Simone.

1397
02:09:31,257 --> 02:09:32,465
Where is Theo?

1398
02:09:33,384 --> 02:09:34,968
I want my husband.

1399
02:09:35,428 --> 02:09:37,637
Theo will be here in less than an hour.

1400
02:09:39,098 --> 02:09:41,349
<i>What is your fondest career memory?</i>

1401
02:09:42,977 --> 02:09:45,061
<i>Every time the curtain goes up.</i>

1402
02:10:00,870 --> 02:10:02,704
<i>Your fondest memory as a woman?</i>

1403
02:10:04,498 --> 02:10:05,957
<i>My first kiss.</i>

1404
02:10:08,461 --> 02:10:09,544
<i>Do you like night time?</i>

1405
02:10:10,171 --> 02:10:12,923
<i>Yes, with a lot of light.</i>

1406
02:10:13,341 --> 02:10:14,215
<i>Dawn?</i>

1407
02:10:15,259 --> 02:10:17,636
<i>With a piano and friends.</i>

1408
02:10:18,137 --> 02:10:19,179
<i>The evening?</i>

1409
02:10:19,889 --> 02:10:22,349
<i>For us, it's dawn.</i>

1410
02:10:28,272 --> 02:10:30,148
See, you're breathing.

1411
02:10:38,324 --> 02:10:39,908
I can't go back.

1412
02:10:44,538 --> 02:10:45,664
I can't.

1413
02:11:25,162 --> 02:11:28,999
<i>If you were to give advice to a woman,
what would it be?</i>

1414
02:11:30,209 --> 02:11:31,292
<i>Love.</i>

1415
02:11:32,044 --> 02:11:33,128
<i>To a young girl?</i>

1416
02:11:33,587 --> 02:11:34,587
<i>Love.</i>

1417
02:11:35,089 --> 02:11:36,089
<i>To a child?</i>

1418
02:11:37,591 --> 02:11:38,591
<i>Love.</i>

1419
02:11:41,846 --> 02:11:43,346
Who are you knitting for?

1420
02:11:45,725 --> 02:11:47,726
Whoever will wear my sweater.

1421
02:11:50,271 --> 02:11:53,857
That's all. I hope it wasn't too long.

1422
02:11:56,402 --> 02:11:57,569
Thank you very much.

1423
02:11:57,862 --> 02:11:59,571
Thank you, young lady.

1424
